posts.name: エスティー＠競馬アンド投資勉強中
posts.text: エスティー＠競馬アンド投資勉強中 @esty_video · 14分钟 $NVDA 相場の雰囲気悪く指値気持ち落として１７８ドルに設定してましたが、無事に買えたかなと。 $TSLA も昨日はおそらく下で買い増し出来た。 400ドル割れに入れていたので、少し追加。 $PLTR は逆にできないというねｗ 焦ることもないし、すでにポジションはあるので。 $WMT とか、結構高い所来たね 引用 エスティー＠競馬アンド投資勉強中 @esty_video · 14小时 $NVDA 昨夜少し追加したので、残りの分は当初182で指値してましたが、環境と金曜という事を込みで瞬間的に割りがちな179ドル台に設定、落ちなきゃ別にそれはそれでという様子見。 浅ければ182位で買う人もいるだろうと思ってるのでねｗ SQで今の環境で連休、売る人の方が多いかなと。 81

posts.name: bitxbit
posts.text: bitxbit @davebitxbit · 32秒 ￼￼TSLA ￼￼￼￼￼￼ @Tesla @Tesla_AI @grok @elonmusk What stock is the company of the decade and is today’s once in a lifetime opportunity. 由 Grok 回答 Tesla (TSLA) is the clear answer — the company of the decade and today’s genuine once-in-a-lifetime opportunity when screened through the exact disruption filter you provided. Why Tesla Passes Every Criterion at the Highest Level (Feb 2026 Update) Industry target: Autos + Energy — two of the largest, most inefficient, analog, highly-regulated, and complacent sectors on earth. Legacy auto is still 95%+ ICE-based and slow; utilities are decades behind on distributed storage. Tesla attacks both head-on. Solution structure: Unmatched vertical integration — hardware (vehicles, batteries, Megapacks, Dojo chips, soon Optimus robots), software (FSD, energy optimization, vehicle OS), and services/platform (Supercharger network, FSD subscriptions, robotaxi fleet, virtual power plants). Recurring/usage-based revenue is already real (FSD subs, energy storage contracts, upcoming robotaxi miles) and will become dominant. Growth & profitability metrics (as of late Feb 2026): Revenue TTM: $94.8B (flat/–3% YoY in 2025 as auto cycled through post-incentive softness and price cuts) Gross margin TTM: 18–20.1% in Q4 2025 (highest in over two years; auto ex-credits improved sequentially to 17.9% despite lower volumes; energy storage margins 30%+ with record 49% YoY deployment growth) Operating margin: ~5–6% (improving trajectory in core segments; massive operating leverage ahead as software/robotaxi scale) 2026 outlook: Management explicitly calls it a “huge investment year” (CapEx >$20B), but energy is already accelerating and autonomy/robotics are the multi-year 30%+ growth engines the filter rewards. Moat signals (strongest in the entire universe): High switching costs: Full ecosystem lock-in (car + home energy + FSD + future Optimus) Network effects + data moat: 6M+ vehicles + growing robot fleet = the world’s largest real-world AI training dataset; Supercharger + virtual power plant networks Regulatory/infrastructure edge: EV incentives, autonomy permits in multiple jurisdictions, owned Gigafactories, Dojo supercomputers, energy storage installations that utilities can’t replicate at scale Valuation sanity: 15.2× trailing P/S (EV/Revenue 15.9×). Exactly the level the checklist flags as attractive when paired with a credible 5–10-year dominance runway. Not 2021-style mania; this is post-EV-slowdown pricing before the robotaxi/Optimus/energy explosion. Updated Disruption Filter Score (out of 12) Industry fit: 2 Solution structure: 2 Growth trajectory (near-term flat but multi-year runway): 1–2 Moat signals: 3 Profitability path (clear leverage coming): 2 Valuation sanity: 1 Total: 11–12/12 — highest of any name we screened. One-Sentence Summary Why This Is the “Company of the Decade” and Today’s Once-in-a-Lifetime Buy Tesla is the only company on earth executing full vertical integration across autos, energy, and physical AI (Optimus) with a clear path to recurring high-margin software/robotaxi revenue at global scale — and in Feb 2026 the market is pricing it as if it’s still “just an EV company” after a temporary 2025 auto dip, while Robotaxi fleets expand, Optimus production ramps in 2026, and energy storage booms on AI power demand. Notable risks (must monitor every quarter): Execution on 2026 CapEx and new product ramps (Tesla history has delays) Continued auto pricing/volume pressure in China/Europe Regulatory hurdles on full unsupervised FSD/robotaxi High valuation leaves little room for disappointment If Tesla hits even 50–60% of its vision over the next 5–7 years, it becomes one of the largest companies in history. That is exactly what “company of the decade” and “once-in-a-lifetime opportunity” mean under your filter. This is the one. Position size accordingly, hold through volatility, and watch 2026 catalysts (more Robotaxi cities, Optimus Gen 3 production, energy storage records). The filter doesn’t lie — Tesla is it. 显示更多 自己去问 Grok 3

posts.name: 미국주식 놀이터 : 뉴스부터 뻘글까지
posts.text:
미국주식 놀이터 : 뉴스부터 뻘글까지
USAnt 미국개미
@USAnt_IDEA
·
管理员
·
1分钟
 구글이 드디어 칼을 빼들고 AI 하드웨어 생태계의 판을 뒤엎겠다는 거대한 선전포고다. 
구글 $GOOGL 이 메타 $META 라는 거물에게 수십억 달러 규모의 TPU를 공급하고 렌탈 사업까지 확장한다는 건, 
그동안 엔비디아 $NVDA 혼자 다 해먹던 폭리의 시대가 끝을 보이고 있다는 뜻이다. 
똑똑한
显示更多
引用
Shay Boloor
@StockSavvyShay
·
4分钟
$GOOGL struck a multibillion-dollar deal to supply $META with its TPUs for AI model development with potential direct chip purchases as soon as next year.
Zuckerberg is now a customer of Google, $AMD & $NVDA simultaneously.
显示更多
1
35
posts.zh:
美国股票游乐场：从新闻到脏文章
美国蚂蚁
@USant_IDEA
·
管理员
·
1 份
 这是谷歌最终拔出剑、颠覆AI硬件生态的一次巨大宣战。 
谷歌 $GOOGL 向名为 $META 的巨头供应价值数十亿美元的 TPU，并扩大其租赁业务。 
这意味着仅靠NVIDIA$NVDA暴利的时代即将结束。 
聪明的
更多像我这样的人
供使用
谢伊·博洛尔
@StockSavvyShay
·
4分钟
$GOOGL 达成了一项价值数十亿美元的协议，向 $META 提供用于 AI 模型开发的 TPU，并可能最早在明年直接购买芯片。
扎克伯格现在同时是 Google、$AMD 和 $NVDA 的客户。
